    \end {tikzcd}


 Indeed, the top two triangles are definitions of \theta  and \theta ',
  the squares are each instances of the interchange law, while the
  triangle and the bottom shape are both instances of the left triangle
  identity. The other direction of invertibility follows by symmetry.

To show that \theta  commutes with the units and counits, we observe
  that the following diagram commutes: 




