 Then F'F\dashv  GG'.

Using whiskered composition, the unit of the
  composite adjunction is \bar {\eta } = 1_C\xrightarrow {\eta } GF\xrightarrow {G\eta ' F} GG'F'F, while the
  counit is \bar {\epsilon } = F'FGG'\xrightarrow {F'\epsilon  G'} F'G' \xrightarrow {\epsilon '}   1_E. It now suffices to establish the triangle
  identities. The left triangle identity is witnessed by commutativity
  of




